FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31008
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1784772170
OL,3,CAndy Burnham unveils #2 bus fare cap
OL,4,Cin pledge to be 'cost-of-living
OL,5,Cgovernment'
OL,7,FOn Tuesday, Burnham said his
OL,8,Fgovernment would remove VAT on
OL,9,Fhousehold electricity bills from
OL,10,FOctober.
OL,12,FHis newly appointed chancellor, John
OL,13,FHealey, acknowledged the policy would
OL,14,Fnot "solve the cost of living" but
OL,15,Fsaid it would help 29 million homes
OL,16,Ffeel better off.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31009
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1784772170
OL,3,CAndy Burnham unveils #2 bus fare cap
OL,4,Cin pledge to be 'cost-of-living
OL,5,Cgovernment'
OL,7,FThe VAT rate on household electricity
OL,8,Fwill be cut from 5% to 0% starting on
OL,9,FOctober 1 for six months until the end
OL,10,Fof the financial year in March. It is
OL,11,Fexpected to take #45 off the annual
OL,12,Fprice cap.
OL,14,FThe policy will cost the Exchequer
OL,15,Faround #850 million in 2026/27, with
OL,16,Fthe government claiming it will be
OL,17,Ffunded by scrapping Starmer's digital
OL,18,FID scheme, despite former minister and
OL,19,FStarmer loyalist Darren Jones claiming
OL,20,Fthe ID scheme was yet to have funding
OL,21,Fallocated.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31010
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1784772170
OL,3,CAndy Burnham unveils #2 bus fare cap
OL,4,Cin pledge to be 'cost-of-living
OL,5,Cgovernment'
OL,7,FConsumer expert Martin Lewis also
OL,8,Fvoiced doubts, saying, "in practice
OL,9,Fpeople won't feel much benefit",
OL,10,Fparticularly as the energy price cap
OL,11,Fis predicted to rise 3.1% in October,
OL,12,Fmeaning the saving will be less
OL,13,Fnoticeable.
